reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Space-Saving Powerhouse! ⚡🔌🏢
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the Extension Cord with Multiple Outlets Surge Protector Power Strip Tower, and I couldn't be happier with my decision. This product has proven to be great for keeping my workspace organized.Pros:Compact Design: This power strip tower is a real space-saver. It stands vertically, allowing it to fit seamlessly into tight spots around my desk without taking up precious surface area.Multiple Outlets: With its six outlets, this power strip tower offers an ample number of slots to accommodate all my devices simultaneously. No more juggling or swapping plugs!Surge Protection: The built-in surge protection is a reassuring feature, especially when dealing with valuable electronics. I feel more confident knowing my devices are safeguarded against sudden power surges.USB Ports: The inclusion of USB ports is a thoughtful touch. Charging my smartphone and tablet has become incredibly convenient, eliminating the need for extra adapters.Sturdy Build: The tower feels well-built and sturdy. The materials used seem durable, and the tower doesn't wobble or tip over even with several bulky plugs attached.Cable Management: The integrated cable management system at the base of the tower keeps all the cords neatly organized and prevents tangling. It's a small detail that makes a big difference in maintaining a clutter-free workspace.LED Indicator: The LED indicator is subtle yet helpful. It lets me know at a glance whether the power strip is functioning properly.Cons:To be honest, it's hard to find any significant downsides to this product. However, if I were to nitpick, the power cord could be a bit longer. This would provide more flexibility in positioning the tower further away from the power outlet.
